===Etymology===

From both Czech ''[[robota]]'' meaning "[[drudgery]]" or "[[servitude]]" and from Slovak ''[[robota]]'' meaning "[[labour]]".  First appeared in a translation of the 1921 science-fiction play [[W:R.U.R. (Rossum's Universal Robots)|R.U.R. (Rossum's Universal Robots)]] by Karel Capek.

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''robot''' (plural: [[robots]])

# A machine that resembles [[human]]s in [[shape]] or [[scope]] of [[function]].
# A machine that operates [[automatically]].
# A machine controlled by an [[fundamentally]] [[ingrained]] computer.
# (''South Africa'') [[traffic light|Traffic lights]].

